---
description: Clean code review rule based on imported external guidance
alwaysApply: false
---

Use this rule when reviewing new or changed code for readability and maintainability.

Check:
- names are clear and specific
- functions are small and focused
- side effects are explicit
- duplication is removed only when it improves clarity
- abstractions are not speculative
- tests cover changed behavior
- public APIs remain understandable

